        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Adults present with significant\nfacial trauma\nand\nnasal fracture\nDark purple hematoma against septum\nCommon symptoms in peds, usually within first 24-72 hrs with even minor nasal trauma, include:\nNasal obstruction (95%)\nPain (50%)\nRhinorrhea\n(25%)\nFever\n(25%)",
